  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into thin slices, lengthways&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a matching lid, with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;</span>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5 min, moving the aubergine around the pan occasionally to colour slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>couscous</strong> to a heatproof bowl, cover with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]&nbsp;</span><strong>boiled water</strong>, cover and set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>harissa paste</strong>&nbsp;(can't handle the heat, go easy!) and <strong>honey</strong>&nbsp;with&nbsp;200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong> and stir to combine &ndash; this is your<strong> harissa stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> to the aubergine pan</p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and reduce the heat to medium</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 10 min or until the aubergine is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile&nbsp;(for your garlic crisps),&nbsp;peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lay a few sheets of <strong>kitchen paper</strong> ready at the side of your pan and grab a slotted spoon</p>\r\n<p>Heat a wok or small pan with 3-5 tbsp <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (separating them as you go) and cook until crispy and slightly golden</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>fried garlic</strong> to the kitchen paper (keep the oil for later) and sprinkle them with <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/457.step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip the <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from the stems and chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Fluff the <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork, add a drizzle of the <strong>garlic oil</strong> and mix through</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
